Title: Zaangazowanie Zgromadzenia Salezjanskiego na rzecz rozwoju spolecznego. Wczoraj i dzis/The Involvement of the Salesian Congregation in Social Development. The Then and Now
Abstract: This article applies to the social dimension of the Salesian mission. Subject was, chronologically, included
in the three points. The article begins with the presentation of the social aspect of the life of the Founder of the
Salesians – St. John Bosco. Then it moves to the activity of Bl. Michael Rua and the contribution of other saints,
the servants of God and candidates for sainthood from the Salesian Family. The last point indicates a variety of
pro-social activities in the above mentioned areas in recent years. This article, of which the author is the Postulator
for the Causes of Saints of the Salesian Family, is a contribution to the celebration of 150th anniversary of the
Salesian Congregation (1859 – 2009).   
